<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>break one’s silence • break the silence</xh5><p> <i>break one’s silence—</i>1. finally bring up a subject: Charlotte described the telephone call with which the kidnappers had <u>broken their silence</u>. 2. say smth. after a long pause in conversation: Enoch sat hunched and brooding, <u>breaking his silence</u> only to pass the time of day with John Biffen.</p><p> <i>break the silence</i>— = break one’s silence 2: Everything was quiet and time seemed to stand still until Jill <u>broke the silence</u> saying that Dave had won.</p> </entry>
